# INTRODUCING JOTION : JOURNEY OF THOUGHTS, IDEAS, AND ORGANIZED NOTES

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**The Inspiration:** In the ever-evolving landscape of productivity tools, one platform has stood out for its versatility and user-friendly design - Jotion. Taking inspiration from Notion's innovative approach to note- taking and collaboration, I embarked on a journey to create Jotion, a personal project that brings the essence of Notion to a new realm.

**The Birth of Jotion:** Motivated by a desire to offer users a seamless and customizable note-taking experience, Jotion was born. With a passion for creating intuitive interfaces and a commitment to fostering productivity, I set out to build a platform that captures the essence of Notion's organizational prowess while adding a touch of uniqueness.

**What Sets Jotion Apart:** Jotion is not merely a replication of Notion; it's a distinct entity tailored to meet the needs of its users. From its sleek and responsive design to its powerful collaboration features, Jotion strives to provide a refreshing take on the digital workspace.

**Features That Shine:** Jotion inherits some of Notion's signature features, such as the flexibility to create different types of content blocks, collaborative editing, and an elegant user interface. Beyond that, it introduces enhancements and personalizations, making it a compelling choice for those seeking a modern note-taking and organization tool.

**A Personal and Collaborative Hub:** Jotion caters to both personal and collaborative needs. Whether you're structuring your personal thoughts, managing projects, or collaborating with a team, Jotion adapts to your

workflow seamlessly. The goal is to empower users to create, organize, and share information effortlessly.

**Navigating the Digital Landscape:** As we navigate the digital landscape, the need for efficient and intuitive tools becomes paramount. Jotion aims to be that go-to platform, providing users with a centralized space for their thoughts, ideas, and projects. Its ease of use and adaptability make it a valuable addition to the toolkit of students, professionals, and creatives alike.

**The Continuing Journey:** Jotion is not just a project; it's an ongoing journey of exploration and refinement. Feedback from users plays a pivotal role in shaping its evolution, ensuring that it continues to meet the dynamic needs of its growing community.

**Join the Jotion Experience:** Whether you're a seasoned Notion user or new to the world of digital note- taking, Jotion invites you to join the experience. Discover a platform that marries functionality with a clean aesthetic, designed to inspire creativity and boost productivity. Welcome to Jotion - where your ideas find a home in the digital realm.

**LOGIN PAGE:** The login page of Jotion presents a clean and user-friendly interface, consisting of key elements for seamless authentication and user engagement.

### Header Section

- - **_Logo:_** The page features a prominent logo in the header, providing brand identity and recognition.
    - **_Login Button:_** Positioned in the header, the "Login" button offers a straightforward entry point for users to access their Jotion accounts using Clerk authentication.

### Authentication Options

- - **_Get Jotion Free Button:_** Adjacent to the login button, a prominent "Get Jotion Free" button encourages users to explore the application further. This button serves as a gateway for both login and sign-up processes.
    - **_GitHub Sign-In:_** A convenient option allows users to sign in using their GitHub accounts, streamlining the authentication process.
    - **_Email & Password Sign-In:_** For users preferring traditional sign-in methods, an option to log in using an email and password combination is available.
    - **_Mode Toggle Button:_** This button provides more convenience for users to switch themes to light or dark mode according to there needs.

### Hero Section

- - **_Marketing Lines:_** The hero section showcases compelling lines that serve marketing purposes, enticing users with the app's unique features and benefits.
    - **_Login/Sign-Up Button:_** A strategically placed button in the hero section invites users to either log in or sign up, catering to both existing and new users.

### Footer Section

- - **_Footer Logo:_** The footer maintains consistency with the brand by featuring the logo, reinforcing Jotion's visual identity.

Upon successful login, users are greeted with the Jotion main screen, designed for intuitive navigation and efficient document management.

### Collapsible Navigation Bar

- - **_Left-Hand Side:_** The left-hand side features a collapsible navigation bar, providing easy access to essential functionalities.
    - **_Log Out Modal:_** At the top of the navigation bar, a modal pops up upon interaction, presenting options, including a "Log Out" button for secure logout.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 20 - Log Out Modal**

### Search Functionality

- - **_Search Bar:_** Directly below the Log Out Modal, a search functionality is integrated into the navigation bar, allowing users to search for their created documents swiftly.
    - **_Shortcut:_** The search can be initiated conveniently by using the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + K.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 21 - Search Modal**

1. **Settings Button: _Settings Icon:_** Positioned beneath the search bar, the Settings button opens a modal when clicked, enabling users to toggle between dark and light themes for a personalized-experience.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 22 - Settings Modal**

### New Page Creation

- - **_Create a New Page Button:_** Following the settings, a dedicated button facilitates the creation of new documents, enhancing user workflow.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 23 - Single Note Tile**

### Document Management

- - **_Document Tiles:_** The main section of the screen showcases tiles representing user- created documents.
    - **_Expandable View:_** Each document tile can be expanded to reveal its children documents, providing a hierarchical and organized view of content.
    - **_Action Buttons:_** Every document tile features two buttons: one for deleting the document and another for creating a new child document, streamlining user interactions.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 24 - Children Notes**

### Trash Section

- - ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**_Trash Button:_** A designated Trash button is available for accessing deleted notes. Clicking the button opens a modal displaying all deleted notes, along with a search functionality for quick retrieval.

**Figure 25 - Delete Modal**

### Welcome Section

- - **_User Greeting:_** At the center of the main screen, a welcoming section displays a personalized greeting to the user, creating a friendly and engaging atmosphere.
    - **_Create a Note Button:_** A prominent button labeled "Create a Note" is positioned below the user greeting, encouraging users to initiate the note creation process with a single click.

### Note Creation and Editing Overview

Upon creating a new note in Jotion, users are directed to the note editor, providing a feature-rich environment for content creation and customization.

### Navbar and Title

- - _Title Display:_ At the top of the note, a navbar displays the title of the note. Initially set to "Untitled," users can customize the title of their note.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Figure 26 - Title Textfield**

- - _Publish Button:_ On the extreme right side of the navbar, a "Publish" button is prominently positioned. Clicking this button enables users to publish their note, generating a unique URL for global accessibility. Once published, the note becomes viewable by anyone with the URL, ensuring a secure and unmodifiable presence.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Figure 27 – Publish and Unpublish**

### Menu Button

- - _Menu Icon:_ Adjacent to the "Publish" button, the "Menu" button, when clicked, triggers a modal with options, including the ability to delete the note.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 28 - Delete Modal**

### Add Icon and Add Cover

- - _Hover Effects:_ Below the navbar, hovering the mouse reveals two buttons: "Add Icon" and "Add Cover."

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Figure 29 - Add Icon and Cover Button**

- - _Add Icon:_ Clicking the "Add Icon" button opens a modal displaying a variety of icons for users to choose from, allowing personalization of the note.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 30 - Add Icon Modal**

- - _Add Cover:_ Clicking the "Add Cover" button initiates a popup, enabling users to select an image from their local system to serve as the cover image for the note.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 31 - Cover Image Modal**

### Main Title and Editor

- - _Main Title Section:_ Below the navbar and icon/cover buttons, the main title of the note is displayed prominently.
    - _Editor Space:_ The majority of the screen is dedicated to the note editor, offering a versatile space for content creation.
    - _Slash Command:_ Typing a forward slash ("/") within the editor triggers a modal presenting various options, including three types of headings, list formatting (bullets or numbered), image uploading, and more.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Figure 32 - Slash Popup**
